Hi everyone!

I think I will leave the title for you readers to try and suss out, I can't and I need your help!  Anyhow, this was my 50th game against the Master Mater and I hate to say it but I played loads better against him in my first game and that was when I had a Class C rating!  Here I made the mistake of using the analyse board feature but not analysing it far enough!  Anyhow, on with the game where I kick off with e4.

13. Nb6??? - eeek, eeek and treble eeek!  I will have knightmares about this for years to come.  Now, the move looked OK at first.  I did spot 13...... Nxd4 and the family fork on c2 after I play 14. NxR but I thought that I could get away with it by moving Henry to d2 and if 15......NxQ, 16.  NxQ+.  But I bally would have to overlook 15...... Bb4+ wouldn't I?  Doh and Double Doh!
